{"word":"ἀντιμεθίστημι","slug":"ἀντιμεθίστημι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀντιμεθίστημι</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to move from one side to the other, to revolutionise</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, with <a href='S:aorist tense'>aor.</a> 2 and <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a>, <i>to pass over to the other side</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}